sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J58101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter activated synergistically by cI and CRP with the reporter RFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A promoter activated synergistically by cI and CRP proteins (part ref. BBa_J58011) with a generator of the reporter RFP (part ref. BBa_I13507). This generator uses the following parts: BBa_B0034 (RBS), BBa_E1010 (mRFP1), and BBa_B0015 (Terminator). With this construction, we obtain an AND gate, with RFP as output, and cI and CRP as inputs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Valencia iGEM 2006

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Notice that in the promoter sequence the XbaI restricction site is present. Therefore, we have to digest this part upstream only with EcoRI.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J58103
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mutated promoter activated by OmpR-P with the reporter GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Many signalling cellular processes occur using a phosphorylation mechanism. In order to assemble a transmembranal pathway, that frees a phosphore, with a genetic network within the cell, we can use this promoter (R0083). That promoter is regulated positively (activated) by the transcription factor OmpR-P, and it contains only one operator in its sequence, whereas in the natural promoter (R0082) there are three. We put a well known protein downstream: GFP (E0040) with a RBS (B0034) and a Terminator (B0015). This composite part will be very useful to characterize many cellular biosensors, jointly with the part J58102.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is derived from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the operator site and activates transcription. This is a truncated version of BBa_R0082.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: NC_000193 E. coli K12
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter deletes the C2 and C3 regions of BBa_R0082 (bases 37-74 in BBa_R0082) and inserts an 8-base linker before the -35 and -10 signal region. The efficacy of this promoter versus the full ompC upstream region (BBa_R0082) or the ompF upstream region (BBa_R0084) is currently unknown. The a at base 41 is mutated to t to avoid XbaI site. Speculation that this was a previous assembly site.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: NC_000193 E. coli K12
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The promoter includes the three OmpR binding sites: C1, C2, and C3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1.
An alternate version, BBa_R0083, cuts out the C2 and C3 sites.
The efficacy of this promoter versus the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) or the ompF upstream region (BBa_R0084) is currently unknown.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: NC_000193 E. coli K12
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The promoter includes the three OmpR binding sites: C1, C2, and C3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1.
An alternate version, BBa_R0083, cuts out the C2 and C3 sites.
The efficacy of this promoter versus the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) or the ompF upstream region (BBa_R0084) is currently unknown.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is derived from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the operator site and activates transcription. This is a truncated version of BBa_R0082.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: NC_000193 E. coli K12
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter deletes the C2 and C3 regions of BBa_R0082 (bases 37-74 in BBa_R0082) and inserts an 8-base linker before the -35 and -10 signal region. Speculation that this was a previous assembly site.
